cle legal ethics and elimination of bias workshop stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff calendar cle legal ethics and elimination of bias workshop go back details september 12 2008 from 1 00 pm 4 00 pm stanford law school's center on the legal profession and the john and terry levin center for public service and public interest are co sponsoring a free cle program for our community partners and the law school community professor deborah rhode and professor larry marshall will lead the two part workshop the first two hours will focus on legal ethics and the last hour will address elimination of bias the ethics session will discuss issues of resources and triage that face public interest attorneys there will also be a discussion of particular ethics issues faced by public interest attorneys including issues presented by the attendees for the elimination of bias session the professors will present a series of hypotheticals and discuss whether it is appropriate to take a lawyer's or a client's race gender or ethnicity into account the workshop will also address the issue of cross cultural competence please rsvp to esther ng by sending an e mail to esng law stanford edu no later than wednesday september 10 2008 contact esther ng esng law stanford edu 650 721 2101 related john and terry levin center for public service and public interest law stanford center on the legal profession cloudy 52 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
